# DriveCare Frontend Environment Variables

# ─── Backend API URL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT: Change this to your computer's IP address to use the app anywhere!
#
# How to find your IP:
#   Windows: Open CMD and type "ipconfig" - look for IPv4 Address
#   Mac/Linux: Open Terminal and type "ifconfig" - look for inet address
#
# Then replace localhost with your IP address below:

# For same WiFi network (recommended for development):
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5000/api

# For Android Emulator (if using emulator):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:5000/api

# For iOS Simulator (if using simulator):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5000/api

# For Production (when backend is deployed):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend.railway.app/api

# ─── Instructions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Copy this file to .env (remove .example)
# 2. Replace 192.168.1.100 with YOUR computer's IP address
# 3. Restart Expo: npx expo start --clear
# 4. Test login with demo account (demo@drivecare.com / Demo1234)
